## ⚠️ CRITICAL EXPLOIT: GROUP/UNGROUP CHARACTER OWNERSHIP

**THE CHARACTER MANIPULATION EXPLOIT:**
The group/ungroup sequence can claim ownership of ANY parts, including player character parts!

```lua
-- Get Building Tools endpoint
local bt = workspace[player.Name]["Building Tools"]  -- must be equipped
local ep = bt.SyncAPI.ServerEndpoint
local character = player.Character

-- Step 1: Group the character (or specific parts)
ep:InvokeServer("CreateGroup", "Model", workspace, {character})
wait(0.05)

-- Step 2: Ungroup to claim ownership
ep:InvokeServer("Ungroup", {character})

-- Step 3: Wait for RRPartOwner to be added
for _, part in ipairs(character:GetChildren()) do
    if part:IsA("BasePart") then
        repeat task.wait(0.01) until part:FindFirstChild("RRPartOwner")
    end
end

-- Step 4: Now you can modify character parts with F3X!
-- Change colors
ep:InvokeServer("SyncColor", { [1] = { Part=character.Head, Color=Color3.new(1,0,0) } })

-- Change materials
local SyncAPI = bt.SyncAPI
SyncAPI:Invoke("SyncMaterial", { [1] = { Part=character.Torso, Material=Enum.Material.Neon } })

-- Add meshes
ep:InvokeServer("CreateMeshes", { [1] = { Part=character["Left Arm"] } })
SyncAPI:Invoke("SyncMesh", { [1] = { Part=character["Left Arm"], MeshId="rbxassetid://123456" } })

-- All changes replicate to other players!
```

**Why this works:**
- F3X's group/ungroup doesn't validate ownership before grouping
- Ungrouping triggers the ownership claim system
- RRPartOwner gets added to all parts in the group
- Once owned, all F3X modification APIs work on those parts

**Use cases:**
- Character customization (colors, materials, meshes, textures)
- Body part removal/modification
- Avatar manipulation that replicates to all players
- Creating custom character appearances

